cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on applying reinforcement learning to robotics problems with sparse rewards. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a model-free approach for reinforcement learning using demonstrations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing intelligent agents that can learn from demonstrations and interact with their environment. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper mentions using a robot kinesthetically force-controlled by a human demonstrator to collect demonstrations, which may involve computer vision techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with controlling robotic systems using reinforcement learning.
